          "distinct": false,
          "id": "6ef50bc0264e92bc89bf3c77cf9f488af71a3d25",
          "message": "Add user guide for OPL (#3182)\n\n# Change Summary\n\n<!--\nReplace with a brief summary of the change in this PR\n-->\n\nAdds a comprehensive user guide for the OpenTelemetry Processing\nLanguage (OPL) as an [mdBook](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook)\nproject under crates/query-engine-languages/docs/opl-book/.\n\nPages\n- Introduction -- pipeline syntax, comments, available sources\n- Data Model & Types -- signal types, record structure\n(logs/spans/metrics), attributes, value types, literals, operators\n- Basic Operators -- where filtering, set/extend assignment, value type\nchecks, cardinality constraints\n- Attribute Operators -- rename/project-rename, remove/project-away, and\napply for bulk attribute processing\n- Flow Control -- if/else if/else conditionals, is Log/is Metric/is Span\nsignal type checks, route_to output routing\n- Function Reference -- string, hashing, encoding, math, date/time,\nUUID, and null-handling functions\n- OTTL Comparison -- side-by-side migration guide mapping OTTL editors\nand converters to OPL equivalents, with a list of OTTL capabilities not\nyet available in OPL\n\n\n## What issue does this PR close?\n\n<!--\nWe highly recommend correlation of every PR to an issue\n-->\n\n* Closes #3183\n\n## How are these changes tested?\n\nn/a (docs only)\n\n## Are there any user-facing changes?\n\nno\n\n <!-- If yes, provide further info below -->\n\n### Changelog\n\n<!--\nUser-facing changes need a .chloggen/*.yaml entry. Copy the\nTEMPLATE.yaml\nin go/.chloggen/ or rust/otap-dataflow/.chloggen/ and fill in the\nfields.\nIf not required, include `chore` in the PR title.\n-->\n\n* [x] Added a `.chloggen/*.yaml` entry, OR this PR is a `chore`\n(indicated in title).\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Laurent Qu├®rel <laurent.querel@gmail.com>\nCo-authored-by: Copilot Autofix powered by AI <175728472+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>",
