          "id": "8e04dd217e993c623f05ccbe1d95cc5d5e4b2929",
          "message": "chore(docs): add RFC process + RFC 0001 component-inventory macro (#3434)\n\n# Change Summary\n\nAdds a lightweight **RFC process** for `otap-dataflow` and the first\nRFC,\n**RFC 0001: component-inventory**, proposing a `#[component_inventory]`\nattribute macro for automated component tracking (threat-model drift\ndetection,\ndocumentation coverage, and security review).\n\nThis PR is **documentation only** ŌĆö it adds the RFC process and the\nproposal\ntext so the SIG can review the design before any implementation begins.\nNo code\nis added or changed.\n\nFiles:\n\n- `rust/otap-dataflow/rfcs/README.md` ŌĆö the RFC process: when an RFC is\nneeded,\nthe PR-first lifecycle, serial numbering (independent of PR numbers),\nand file\nnaming. Complements the existing \"design consensus\" note in\n`CONTRIBUTING.md`,\n  which had no formal mechanism.\n- `rust/otap-dataflow/rfcs/0000-template.md` ŌĆö reusable RFC template\n  (Rust/OpenDAL structure).\n- `rust/otap-dataflow/rfcs/0001-component-inventory.md` ŌĆö the proposal.\n\n## The proposal in brief\n\nA `#[component_inventory]` attribute macro in `otap-df-engine-macros` (a\nthird\nmacro alongside the existing `#[pipeline_factory]` and `#[capability]`),\na\n`ComponentMeta` + `COMPONENT_INVENTORY` distributed slice in\n`otap-df-engine`\n(mirroring the existing `#[capability]` ŌåÆ `KNOWN_CAPABILITIES`\nmechanism), and a\n`cargo xtask component-inventory` command with a baseline check. Zero\nruntime\ncost; no new crates.\n\nKey design points for review:\n\n- **`id` is the component's existing URN.** Factory statics already\ncarry a\nunique URN in their `name` field, so the macro reuses it ŌĆö contributors\nwrite\n  no id. Non-factory components (admin server, controller, dfctl, memory\n  limiter) use explicit URN-shaped ids.\n- **`category` is a compile-time enum**, cross-checked against the URN\nsegment,\n  to prevent misspellings like `Reciever` from silently corrupting the\n  inventory.\n- **No `trust_zone`** ŌĆö the engine is trust-boundary-agnostic; trust\nzones are a\n  downstream deployment concern.\n- **Open question left for the SIG:** how strongly to type the\n`attributes` map\n(Options A/B/C in the RFC ŌĆö key constants / typed fields + overflow /\nflat map\n  with macro-validated values).\n\n## What issue does this PR close?\n\nRelates to #3435 (implementation tracking issue). This PR adds the RFC\nitself;\nit does not close an issue -- acceptance is by merge of the RFC, and\n#3435\ntracks the follow-up implementation.\n\n## How are these changes tested?\n\nN/A ŌĆö documentation only. Markdown files, no code.\n\n## Are there any user-facing changes?\n\nNo. This is a design proposal; no runtime, API, or config changes.\n\n### Changelog\n\n* [ ] Added a `.chloggen/*.yaml` entry\n* [ ] This PR is a `chore` (indicated in title)\n* [x] This is a documentation-only PR.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Laurent Qu├®rel <laurent.querel@gmail.com>\nCo-authored-by: Laurent Qu├®rel <l.querel@f5.com>",
