          "id": "df03b91737370ddb38fc93f8fe223281b7de41a7",
          "message": "Updated Experimental ClickHouse Exporter (#3291)\n\nextended from @clhain's PR\n(https://github.com/open-telemetry/otel-arrow/pull/2646)\n\n# Change Summary\n\nThis draft PR includes an experimental implementation of a ClickHouse\nexporter that is an iteration on the previous PR\n(https://github.com/open-telemetry/otel-arrow/pull/2646). Notably:\n- Removed JSON support (It's not recommended at scale yet for OTel data)\n- Uses the official ClickHouse Rust client with Arrow extension\n- Uses HTTP instead of TCP\n\n## How are these changes tested?\n\nUnit tests and an E2E test, but may need better coverage\n\n## Are there any user-facing changes?\n\nNot yet\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Chris Hain <c.hain@f5.com>\nCo-authored-by: David Dahl <d.dahl@f5.com>\nCo-authored-by: clhain <8164192+clhain@users.noreply.github.com>\nCo-authored-by: Swapnil Ashtekar <46826200+swashtek@users.noreply.github.com>\nCo-authored-by: Laurent Qu├®rel <l.querel@f5.com>",
