          "distinct": false,
          "id": "b79ac145a43357630ae611fee70a95882e84be07",
          "message": "fix(otap-exporter): resolve shutdown deadlock when stream queues are full (#3411)\n\nFixes a critical deadlock in `OTAPExporter` that caused it to hang\nindefinitely during shutdown.\n\n**Root Cause**\n\nThis edge case was introduced in #2764. When the downstream receiver is \nunreachable and stream queues are full, the main exporter loop blocks\ninside\n`enqueue_stream_batch` on `sender.reserve()` ŌĆö preventing it from ever\npolling\nthe `Shutdown` control message, resulting in a permanent hang.\n\n**Fix**\n\n- Replaced `sender.reserve().await` with `tokio::select!` that\nconcurrently\nwaits on queue capacity and polls the control channel for shutdown\nsignals\n- Introduced `EnqueueResult` enum so `enqueue_stream_batch` can\npropagate a\n  graceful shutdown without dropping the in-progress batch\n- Wrapped gRPC connection setup in `tokio::select!` to abort cleanly on \n  shutdown, emitting `IncFailed` for any correlated pdata\n\n**Testing**\n\nAdded `test_otap_exporter_deadlock_on_full_queue_shutdown` ŌĆö simulates\nfull\nqueues + unreachable endpoint, asserts shutdown within 200ms. All\nexisting\ntests pass.\n\n**User-facing changes:** None\n\n**Changelog:**\n- [x] Added a `.chloggen/*.yaml` entry\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: albertlockett <a.lockett@f5.com>",
