          "id": "15a17061faa78cb695e10236d7eb329d7e9914e8",
          "message": "ITS metrics integration (#3457)\n\n**Not ready for review**\n\n# Change Summary\n\nRoutes internal metric-set snapshots through the Internal Telemetry\nSystem as OTLP metrics, allowing the observability pipeline to process,\nroute, and export them. The internal telemetry receiver now supports\nperiodic metric emission and exact-match metric views with name and\ndescription overrides.\n\n## What issue does this PR close?\n\n* Closes #2408\n\n## How are these changes tested?\n\n* Unit tests cover registry integration, metric-set-to-OTLP conversion,\nviews, deduplication, and collision handling.\n* Receiver tests cover configuration and periodic metric emission.\n* An integration test validates metric views and periodic export through\nthe internal telemetry pipeline.\n* `cargo xtask check`\n\n### Manual functional validation\n\nCompared an ITS OTLP metrics batch with the unchanged admin metrics\nregistry over the same collection interval. The comparison covered\nmetric values, metadata, instrumentation scopes, and entity attributes.\n\nThe test passed: 78 raw fields across 9 metric-set instances produced 76\nexpected OTLP streams, with empty MMSC fields intentionally omitted. All\nemitted streams matched, and all six configured views were applied only\nto the OTLP output while the admin endpoint retained the original metric\nnames.\n\nThis validates the complete registry -> ITS receiver -> OTLP conversion\nand view-processing path.\n\nNote: In this run, 2 of 8 MMSC fields were omitted:\n- receiver.traffic_generator/smooth.behind.remaining.batches\n- receiver.traffic_generator/smooth.behind.remaining.items\n\nBoth had zero observations because the traffic generator did not fall\nbehind. This accounts for the reduction from 78 raw admin fields to 76\nOTLP streams.\n\n### Internal metrics bridge throughput\n\nMeasured in a release build on an Apple M4 Max (16 cores, 64 GB) using\nmetric sets containing eight mixed fields: counters, gauges, and MMSC\nmetrics.\n\n```\nEntities per batch    Configuration         Batch time    Metric sets/s    OTLP metrics/s\nŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöü  ŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöü  ŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöü  ŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöü  ŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöü\n                100    No views               139.74 ┬Ąs             716k             5.73M\nŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n                100    Six matching views     196.12 ┬Ąs             510k             4.08M\nŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n              1,000    No views               1.4715 ms             680k             5.44M\nŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n              1,000    Six matching views     2.0609 ms             485k             3.88M\n```\n\nAcross both batch sizes, applying six views added approximately 40% to\nbatch processing time and reduced throughput by approximately 29%.\n\nThroughput decreases by approximately 5% for the larger batch in both\nconfigurations. Because the decrease is nearly identical with and\nwithout views, it does not appear to result from nonlinear view\nmatching. It is most likely caused by the larger live working set and\nassociated allocation, cache, and serialization costs.\n\nThe benchmark covers metric-set update and snapshotting, reporter\nenqueueing, collector/registry aggregation, registry draining, and OTLP\nprotobuf encoding. It excludes registration, periodic waiting,\ndownstream pipeline/exporter processing, and network I/O, so these\nresults represent the capacity of the core bridge rather than end-to-end\nexport throughput.\n\nThe benchmark is in benchmarks/benches/internal_metrics_bridge/main.rs\nand can be reproduced with:\n\n`cargo bench -p benchmarks --bench internal_metrics_bridge`\n  \n## Are there any user-facing changes?\n\nYes. Internal metrics can now use `provider: its` (opt-in, SDK is still\nthe default in this PR), with the export interval and supported metric\nviews configured on the internal telemetry receiver.\n\nNote: The OTel Rust Client SDK will be removed in a future PR.\n\n### Changelog\n\n* [x] Added a `.chloggen/*.yaml` entry\n* [ ] This PR is a `chore` (indicated in title)\n* [ ] This is a documentation-only PR.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Copilot Autofix powered by AI <175728472+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>",
