          "distinct": false,
          "id": "998ea0f3380e65973447a18cb473873975415911",
          "message": "feat(metrics): Migrate azure_monitor_exporter metrics to the new item attribute format (#3519)\n\n# Change Summary\n\n<!--Replace with a brief summary of the change in this PR-->\n\n`azure_monitor_exporter` telemetry now reports completion, HTTP attempts\nand latency, state mappings, and heartbeat sends through bounded\n`outcome`, `response`, and `mapping` dimensions. Completion metrics use\nthe shared `items`, `batches`, and `messages` vocabulary and carry fixed\n`signal=\"logs\"` context.\n\n### validation\n\nA traffic-generator sample sends 100 logs, then stops, and fans out to\n`valid_exporter`, which sends to a development DCR, and `mock_exporter`\nconfigured to a nonexistent endpoint.\n\n### `valid_exporter`\n\n| Scope | Evidence |\n| --- | --- |\n| `exporter.azure_monitor.exports` |\n`items_total{outcome=\"success\",signal=\"logs\"} =\n100`<br>`batches_total{outcome=\"success\",signal=\"logs\"} =\n3`<br>`messages_total{outcome=\"success\",signal=\"logs\"} = 10` |\n| `exporter.azure_monitor.http` | `responses_total{response=\"http_2xx\"}\n= 3`<br>`latency_milliseconds_count{response=\"http_2xx\"} =\n3`<br>`latency_milliseconds_sum{response=\"http_2xx\"} = 393` |\n| `exporter.azure_monitor` | `batch_size_bytes_count =\n3`<br>`batch_size_bytes_sum =\n3923`<br>`batch_uncompressed_size_bytes_count =\n3`<br>`batch_uncompressed_size_bytes_sum = 24913`<br>`in_flight_exports\n= 0`<br>`in_flight_log_records = 0`<br>`log_entries_too_large_total = 0`\n|\n| `exporter.azure_monitor.state` | `mappings{mapping=\"batch_to_message\"}\n= 1`<br>`mappings{mapping=\"message_to_batch\"} =\n1`<br>`mappings{mapping=\"message_to_data\"} = 1` |\n\n### `mock_exporter`\n\n| Scope | Evidence |\n| --- | --- |\n| `exporter.azure_monitor.exports` |\n`items_total{outcome=\"failure\",signal=\"logs\"} =\n100`<br>`batches_total{outcome=\"failure\",signal=\"logs\"} =\n3`<br>`messages_total{outcome=\"failure\",signal=\"logs\"} = 10` |\n| `exporter.azure_monitor.http` |\n`responses_total{response=\"network_error\"} =\n15`<br>`latency_milliseconds_count{response=\"network_error\"} =\n15`<br>`latency_milliseconds_sum{response=\"network_error\"} = 14` |\n| `exporter.azure_monitor` | `batch_size_bytes_count =\n3`<br>`batch_size_bytes_sum =\n4938`<br>`batch_uncompressed_size_bytes_count =\n3`<br>`batch_uncompressed_size_bytes_sum = 44313`<br>`in_flight_exports\n= 1`<br>`in_flight_log_records = 40`<br>`log_entries_too_large_total =\n0` |\n| `exporter.azure_monitor.state` | `mappings{mapping=\"batch_to_message\"}\n= 1`<br>`mappings{mapping=\"message_to_batch\"} =\n4`<br>`mappings{mapping=\"message_to_data\"} = 4` |\n\n## What issue does this PR close?\n\n* Related to #3300\n\n## How are these changes tested?\n\nUnit tests and local pipeline run\n\n## Are there any user-facing changes?\n\nExporter metric names and dimensions change. Dashboards, alerts, and\nqueries that use the previous `azure_monitor_exporter` metric names must\nmove to the new dimensioned series.\n\n### Changelog\n\n<!--\nUser-facing changes need a .chloggen/*.yaml entry. Copy the\nTEMPLATE.yaml\nin go/.chloggen/ or rust/otap-dataflow/.chloggen/ and fill in the\nfields.\nIf not required, include `chore` in the PR title.\n-->\n\n* [x] Added a `.chloggen/*.yaml` entry\n* [ ] This PR is a `chore` (indicated in title)\n* [ ] This is a documentation-only PR.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Laurent Qu├®rel <l.querel@f5.com>",
