          "distinct": false,
          "id": "6dd7894e48d56006ad0d1e7645a95d9ab42ba209",
          "message": "feat(engine): add BearerTokenAuthorizer capability (#3494)\n\n## Description\n\nAdds the **`BearerTokenAuthorizer`** capability to `otap-df-engine`: a\nrequest-facing access-control trait for data-path nodes (typically\nreceivers) that authenticate callers with an OAuth/OIDC-style bearer\ntoken. It also groups the bearer-token capabilities and the\nauthorization vocabulary they share under a single `capability::auth`\ndomain.\n\n`authorize` performs **authentication and admission behind one call**,\nso a receiver depends on a single capability rather than orchestrating\nthe steps itself:\n\n```rust\nasync fn authorize(&self, credential: &BearerToken)\n    -> Result<AuthzDecision, CapabilityError>;\n```\n\nIt authenticates the token and admits the resulting identity against the\nauthorizer's own policy (e.g. an allow-list). Admission is on the token\nalone; contextual per-request authorization (route, tenant, signal,\naction) is a downstream concern that consumes the emitted identity.\n\n### Types (all under `capability::auth`)\n- **`BearerToken`** ŌĆö one shared credential for both sides of the data\npath: minted and handed out by a `BearerTokenProvider` (carrying an\noptional monotonic expiry so consumers know when to refresh), and\npresented by a caller for a `BearerTokenAuthorizer` to validate (no\nexpiry set ŌĆö freshness is the authorizer's concern). Secret-protecting\n(`SecretString` + `Arc`, redacted `Debug`). Built from a bare token\n(`new`), a known lifetime (`with_expiry` / `from_absolute_expiry`), or a\nwhole `Authorization` header value (`from_header_value`, which strips a\ncase-insensitive `Bearer ` prefix).\n- **`AuthzDecision`** ŌĆö `Allow { identity }` or `Deny { reason, detail\n}`. `reason` is a typed, coarse **`DenyReason`** (`MissingCredential` /\n`InvalidCredential` / `NotPermitted`) that is safe as a low-cardinality\nmetric label; `detail` is an optional free-form string for logs only. A\ndeny is a **normal outcome**, not an error; an `Err` means the\nauthorizer could not reach a decision (e.g. its backend is unreachable)\nand **callers must fail closed**.\n- **`AuthorizedIdentity`** ŌĆö the authenticated principal carried on\n`Allow`, scheme-agnostic (`subject` + `audience`), so a consumer can\npropagate it downstream (e.g. multi-tenant routing). Marked\n`#[non_exhaustive]` since it is the input to downstream authorization\nand is expected to grow (e.g. OIDC groups/claims).\n\n### Design notes\n- **Transport- and library-agnostic** ŌĆö the token is a plain\n`&str`/`BearerToken`, never an HTTP/RPC crate's request type. A receiver\nextracts it from whatever transport it uses.\n- **Caching lives in the implementation** ŌĆö `Allow` carries no validity\nwindow; an authorizer that wants to avoid a per-request backend\nround-trip (e.g. a `TokenReview` call) caches internally, keyed by the\nopaque token with its own TTL. Callers stay simple.\n- **\"No auth\" = capability not bound** ŌĆö there is no bypass flag; a node\nthat wants no authentication simply doesn't bind the capability.\n- **Single export surface** ŌĆö shared data types are re-exported at\n`capability::auth::{BearerToken, AuthzDecision, DenyReason,\nAuthorizedIdentity}` (defining modules private); the registration handle\nis at\n`capability::auth::bearer_token_authorizer::BearerTokenAuthorizer`;\ntrait variants under\n`{local,shared}::capability::auth::bearer_token_authorizer`.\n\n### Scope\nThis PR is the **capability only**. A concrete implementation ŌĆö a\ngeneric Kubernetes service-account-token authorizer (TokenReview-backed)\nŌĆö will follow in a separate PR.\n\n### Testing\n- Unit tests for `BearerToken` construction/header parsing/secret\nredaction and `AuthzDecision`/`AuthorizedIdentity`.\n- `cargo test -p otap-df-engine`, `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo clippy\n--all-targets`: all clean.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>",
