          "distinct": true,
          "id": "c79986e5f5362a88ef30362f26358b47cc4c7166",
          "message": "Remove Rust OTel metrics SDK (#3523)\n\n# Change Summary\n\nRemove the Rust OpenTelemetry metrics SDK path and route internal\nmetrics exclusively through the native ITS metric registry and engine\nobservability pipeline.\n\nThe internal telemetry receiver handles periodic metric export and\nsupported views, while pipeline exporters provide OTLP and OTAP\ndelivery. The default pipeline consumes metrics through a no-op exporter\nand preserves the existing log-provider defaults (could be changed in a\nfuture PR). The registry-backed admin metrics endpoint remains available\n(a Prometheus exporter will be introduced in a future PR).\n\n## What issue does this PR close?\n\n* Closes #2409\n\n## How are these changes tested?\n\n* `cargo xtask check`\n* Unit tests cover metric-set-to-OTLP conversion, views, registry\ndraining and rollback, shutdown behavior, backpressure, and\nobservability-pipeline validation.\n* An end-to-end test verifies periodic registry metrics reach an OTLP\nexporter with selective view transformations.\n* The internal metrics bridge benchmark covers representative batches\nwith and without views.\n\n**Internal metrics performance: Rust SDK vs native ITS**\n\nRelease builds of the pre-PR SDK version (de748c94) and native ITS\nversion (5104df7e) were benchmarked on an Apple M4 Max. The workload\nused four pipeline cores, 50k pre-generated logs/s per core, detailed\ninternal telemetry, two equivalent metric views, and one-second\nOTLP/HTTP exports to a local sink.\n\nEach version ran twice for five minutes after a 30-second warm-up,\nordered SDK ŌåÆ ITS ŌåÆ ITS ŌåÆ SDK.\n\n```\n Metrics path      Mean CPU (range)        Mean RSS (range)     Peak RSS    OTLP exports/run\nŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöü  ŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöü  ŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöü  ŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöü  ŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöüŌöü\n Rust OTel SDK    6.30% (6.14-6.46)               107.6 MiB    111.0 MiB                 299\nŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ  ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n Native ITS       6.23% (6.11-6.35)    98.7 MiB (98.5ŌĆō98.8)    101.8 MiB                 300\n```\n\nCPU usage was effectively unchanged, the 0.07 percentage-point\ndifference is within run-to-run variation. Mean and peak RSS were both\napproximately 8.3% lower with native ITS. Both implementations sustained\napproximately one successful OTLP export per configured interval.\n  \n## Are there any user-facing changes?\n\nYes. This is a breaking configuration change: `engine.telemetry.metrics`\nis no longer supported.\n\nPeriodic export and views must be configured on\n`receiver:internal_telemetry`, with exporters declared as observability\npipeline nodes. Prometheus metrics are now exposed through the admin API\nat the fixed `/api/v1/metrics` path.\n\nSee the [migration\nguide](rust/otap-dataflow/docs/configuration.md#migrating-internal-metrics-from-the-rust-opentelemetry-sdk)\nfor configuration mappings and examples.\n\n### Changelog\n\n* [x] Added a `.chloggen/*.yaml` entry\n* [ ] This PR is a `chore` (indicated in title)\n* [ ] This is a documentation-only PR.",
