          "distinct": false,
          "id": "3c22c5bb487d66bbf1aaca7021db4416b3baaebd",
          "message": "chore(deps): update all patch versions (#3546)\n\nThis PR contains the following updates:\n\n| Package | Type | Update | Change |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| [clap](https://redirect.github.com/clap-rs/clap) |\nworkspace.dependencies | patch | `4.6.3` ŌåÆ `4.6.4` |\n| [libc](https://redirect.github.com/rust-lang/libc) |\nworkspace.dependencies | patch | `0.2.188` ŌåÆ `0.2.189` |\n| [pest](https://pest.rs/)\n([source](https://redirect.github.com/pest-parser/pest)) |\nworkspace.dependencies | patch | `2.8.7` ŌåÆ `2.8.8` |\n| [pest_derive](https://pest.rs/)\n([source](https://redirect.github.com/pest-parser/pest)) |\nworkspace.dependencies | patch | `2.8.7` ŌåÆ `2.8.8` |\n| [tokio-stream](https://tokio.rs)\n([source](https://redirect.github.com/tokio-rs/tokio)) |\nworkspace.dependencies | patch | `0.1.18` ŌåÆ `0.1.19` |\n\n---\n\n### Release Notes\n\n<details>\n<summary>clap-rs/clap (clap)</summary>\n\n###\n[`v4.6.4`](https://redirect.github.com/clap-rs/clap/compare/clap_complete-v4.6.3...clap_complete-v4.6.4)\n\n[Compare\nSource](https://redirect.github.com/clap-rs/clap/compare/v4.6.3...v4.6.4)\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>rust-lang/libc (libc)</summary>\n\n###\n[`v0.2.189`](https://redirect.github.com/rust-lang/libc/releases/tag/0.2.189)\n\n[Compare\nSource](https://redirect.github.com/rust-lang/libc/compare/0.2.188...0.2.189)\n\n##### Added\n\n- Emscripten: Add `pthread_sigmask`, `sigwait`, `sigwaitinfo`,\n`sigtimedwait`, `faccessat`, and `pthread_kill`\n([#&#8203;5270](https://redirect.github.com/rust-lang/libc/pull/5270))\n- Linux SPARC: Enable the `clone3` syscall\n([#&#8203;4980](https://redirect.github.com/rust-lang/libc/pull/4980))\n- Solarish: Add `CLOCK_PROCESS_CPUTIME_ID` and `CLOCK_THREAD_CPUTIME_ID`\n([#&#8203;5274](https://redirect.github.com/rust-lang/libc/pull/5274))\n\n##### Deprecated\n\n- Deprecate `CLONE_INTO_CGROUP` and `CLONE_CLEAR_SIGHAND`. These\noverflow their types and will be changed to a larger size in the future.\n([8c6e6710458d](https://redirect.github.com/rust-lang/libc/commit/8c6e6710458db4d6aa0766f6f84bbf13f640237e))\n\n##### Fixed\n\n- Musl riscv32: Rename padding fields to avoid a conflict and fix the\nbuild\n([2499ff0ad993](https://redirect.github.com/rust-lang/libc/commit/2499ff0ad9936a036e78a4e0991445efee383564))\n- NuttX: Fix `wchar_t` definition under Arm\n([#&#8203;5245](https://redirect.github.com/rust-lang/libc/pull/5245))\n- Windows: Add back link names for `time`-related symbols\n([#&#8203;5300](https://redirect.github.com/rust-lang/libc/pull/5300))\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>pest-parser/pest (pest)</summary>\n\n###\n[`v2.8.8`](https://redirect.github.com/pest-parser/pest/releases/tag/v2.8.8)\n\n[Compare\nSource](https://redirect.github.com/pest-parser/pest/compare/v2.8.7...v2.8.8)\n\n##### What's Changed\n\n- Fix tag\\_node incorrectly modifying tokens during lookahead by\n[@&#8203;tomtau](https://redirect.github.com/tomtau) in\n[#&#8203;1180](https://redirect.github.com/pest-parser/pest/pull/1180)\n\n**Full Changelog**:\n<https://github.com/pest-parser/pest/compare/v2.8.7...v2.8.8>\n\n##### Warning: Semantic Versioning\n\nNote that the node tag feature in 2.6.0 was a technically\nsemver-breaking change even though it is a backwards-compatible /\nnon-breaking change in the meta-grammar. There may be similar\nnon-breaking changes to the meta-grammar between minor versions in the\nfuture. These non-breaking changes, however, may translate into\nsemver-breaking changes due to the additional variants propagated from\nthe generated `Rule` enum.\n\nThis new feature caused issues in some Cargo version resolution\nsituations where Cargo mixed different versions of pest dependencies.\nFor this reason, these \"grammar non-breaking but semver-breaking\"\nchanges are now available only under the \"grammar-extras\" feature flag.\nIf you would like to use node tags (or other future grammar features),\nyou can do so by enabling this flag on the pest\\_derive crate in your\nCargo.toml:\n\n```\n...\npest_derive = { version = \"2.8\", features = [\"grammar-extras\"] }\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>tokio-rs/tokio (tokio-stream)</summary>\n\n###\n[`v0.1.19`](https://redirect.github.com/tokio-rs/tokio/compare/tokio-stream-0.1.18...tokio-stream-0.1.19)\n\n[Compare\nSource](https://redirect.github.com/tokio-rs/tokio/compare/tokio-stream-0.1.18...tokio-stream-0.1.19)\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n### Configuration\n\n­¤ōģ **Schedule**: (UTC)\n\n- Branch creation\n  - \"before 8am every weekday\"\n- Automerge\n  - At any time (no schedule defined)\n\n­¤Ü” **Automerge**: Disabled by config. Please merge this manually once you\nare satisfied.\n\nŌÖ╗ **Rebasing**: Whenever PR becomes conflicted, or you tick the\nrebase/retry checkbox.\n\n­¤æ╗ **Immortal**: This PR will be recreated if closed unmerged. Get\n[config\nhelp](https://redirect.github.com/renovatebot/renovate/discussions) if\nthat's undesired.\n\n---\n\n- [ ] <!-- rebase-check -->If you want to rebase/retry this PR, check\nthis box\n\n---\n\nThis PR was generated by [Mend Renovate](https://mend.io/renovate/).\nView the [repository job\nlog](https://developer.mend.io/github/open-telemetry/otel-arrow).\n\n<!--renovate-debug:eyJjcmVhdGVkSW5WZXIiOiI0My4yNzIuNCIsInVwZGF0ZWRJblZlciI6IjQzLjI3NS4yIiwidGFyZ2V0QnJhbmNoIjoibWFpbiIsImxhYmVscyI6WyJkZXBlbmRlbmNpZXMiXX0=-->\n\nCo-authored-by: renovate[bot] <29139614+renovate[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>",
